Explanation:

I examined the route and controller code to determine which parameters the POST /api/products/{id}/reviews endpoint expects.

- Path parameter:
  - The route is defined as /api/products/:id/reviews and uses the checkObjectId middleware, so a required path parameter "id" (a Mongoose ObjectId, represented as a string) is required.

- Authentication:
  - The route is protected by the protect middleware which reads the JWT from req.cookies.jwt. In HTTP requests cookies are sent via the Cookie header, so a header parameter named "Cookie" carrying the jwt cookie is required to authenticate the request.

- Body payload:
  - The controller reads rating and comment from req.body and uses them to create a review. The product review schema requires rating (number) and comment (string), so the request body must be a JSON object with those two required properties. Other review fields (name, user) are set server-side and should not be supplied.

Based on the above, the operation parameters (Swagger 2.0 Parameter Objects) are the path parameter "id", a header parameter "Cookie" to carry the jwt cookie, and a body parameter "review" whose schema contains required properties rating and comment.

